    <text id="A2915T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>In this letter to her brother, Margaret writes of efforts to start a petition to
                    get Enos out of the army as well as the efforts of neighbors to harvest their
                    crops. In the postscript, she mentions Confederate efforts to impress slaves
                    from citizens and her refusal to send their slave, Alf, off to them.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Moffetts Creek V<hi rend="super">a</hi><lb/>Dec 7<lb/>Mr Enos Ott<lb/>Camp
                    Lee<lb/>Richmond<lb/>V<hi rend="super">a</hi><lb/>Care Rev H. Brown
                    <name type="recipient">Mr Enos Ott</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-12-06">December 6<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1864</date>
                        <name type="place">Willow Row</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Brother</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>we are all well and doing very well consider<add hand="h1" place="inline"
                    >ing</add> every thing. Jinnie and I received your letter saturday I was at the
                        <orig reg="office">offis</orig> when the stage <orig reg="came">come</orig>
                    I saw John W. Henry and Frank M<hi rend="super">c</hi>Nutt come home last
                    saturday <orig reg="evening">evning</orig> on detail for 20 days and I think
                    very <orig reg="likely">likeley</orig> he can get his detail extended. he got it
                    to come home and bail his hay and get up his corn and <orig reg="gather"
                    >gether</orig> up all he can. Elec went home last week he <orig reg="brought"
                        >brot</orig> a man down with him to help put up corn or to do <orig
                        reg="any">aney</orig> thing we have for him to do he is not very smart he
                    never says <orig reg="any">aney</orig> thing with out we ask him questions. they
                    are <orig reg="putting">puting</orig> up corn every day the weather will admit.
                    Old Peet and Barkley <orig reg="won't">wont</orig> work half the time we <orig
                        reg="expect">exspect</orig> to butcher tomorrow. Frank M<hi rend="super"
                    >c</hi>Nutt was here yesterday he says Miss Ann R. <abbr expan="McNutt">M<hi
                            rend="super">c</hi>.</abbr> is not well she has sore <orig reg="throat"
                        >throt</orig> Doctor Bill has moved in M<hi rend="super">r</hi> Robert M<hi
                        rend="super">c</hi>Nutts house <pb n="2"/>M<hi rend="super">r</hi> Black and
                    James Cooper went to town to day with your account book. we had been talking
                        <orig reg="about">a bout</orig>
                    <orig reg="getting">geting</orig> up a <orig reg="petition">petion</orig> and
                    sending down to <orig reg="Richmond">Ritchmond</orig> to get you off. I was very
                    glad to hear that you got your box we were very <orig reg="fearful"
                    >fearfull</orig> that some one <orig reg="might">mite</orig> brake it open, but
                    it was a very <orig reg="common">commen</orig> looking box they <orig
                        reg="thought">thaught</orig>
                    <orig reg="there">thare</orig>
                    <orig reg="wasn't">wasent</orig>
                    <orig reg="much">mutch</orig> in it. well I must close hoping to see you home
                    soon.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>yours most <orig reg="truly">truley</orig></salute>
                    <signed>Maggi H Ott</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">PS they are drafting the negros they <orig reg="notified"
                            >notifyed</orig> me to report Alf last friday I got M<hi rend="super"
                        >r</hi> Black attend to it for me I told him I could not spare him <orig
                            reg="Doctor">Docter</orig> M<hi rend="super">c</hi>Chesney went to town
                        saturday to hire a <orig reg="hand">han</orig> we under stood he did not get
                            <orig reg="any">aney</orig> I do not know what <orig reg="they're"
                        >there</orig> going to make of it. Henry says <orig reg="positively"
                            >posatively</orig> Alf is not to <orig reg="go">got</orig>. Jinnie and
                        Charlott <orig reg="send">sends</orig>
                        <orig reg="their">there</orig> love to you. Your sister Mag.</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
